{
  "texts": [
    "The traditional method of generating the feature vector is to use a one-hot vector that represents unique words with '0' for the non-target word and '1' for the target word.",
    "The problem with these representations is that they cannot build relationships among words.",
    "Existing studies [55, 56, 59 ] have shown that using word embeddings outperforms manual feature selection for the NER tasks.",
    "Word2vec [21] is a widely used word embedding that incorporates the information of skip-grams or continuous bag-ofwords.",
    "While word2vec outperforms traditional methods of generating word embeddings, it still lacks information such as n-grams."
  ]
}